This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image processing and segmentation. The use of Deep Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the design of loss functions and the integration of external data, which are common topics in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The use of Normalized Cuts technique within a deep network also suggests that it could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the integration of the boundary detector with semantic segmentation, which could place it in the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
